@turcsanyip confirmed with the SDK team that getDirectoryClient(“”) is valid. Made the change in property to allow empty string.
Removed PROP_ for SAS_TOKEN
Updated to catch Exception and tested the scenario. I was able to see the failure files with a non-existing filesystem.

@si-sun What JIRA is this associated with?  We need the commit heading to reference the NIFI jIRA.

Please create a JIRA here https://issues.apache.org/jira/projects/NIFI/issues and update the commit message to reflect that. The PR itself looks good.

Only thing that jumped out is we might not include the nar in the default assembly due to size concerns but I'll check that.

Merging to master...
Also fix the CRLF line endings during the merge.
@MuazmaZ Could you please use LF endings in your future commits? Thanks

@si-sun thanks.  The commit message should reflect the JIRA involved.  So instead of it saying "Adding GetSmbFile and PutSmbFile processors" it should say "NIFI-7338 Adding GetSmbFile and PutSmbFile processors". You can see this in the PR notice text we provide and the contribution guide.

This is important because it causes the linkage of the commit to the JIRA to occur which greatly helps with release processes and tracking provenance of changes/etc..

I can do this if it gets merged but want to make sure you know this for future contributions or if you end up needing to add a commit to this.

@mattyb149 
Changes look good and straightforward here.  We should have these mirrored in https://github.com/apache/nifi/blob/master/nifi-docker/dockerhub/sh/start.sh.  What would be more correct in the longer term is to structure our Docker images such that we could reuse one copy.  Believe I created a ticket at some point to address this but doesn't need to happen within this particular issue as it is certainly more involved.

As long as we provide the same configurability for the image we publish to Hub, looks good to me.

> @natural Would you be able to snag the tests from #4207 and make the change to the logic and zookeeper.properties and then we'll just turn the other PR into the client path?

@jfrazee thank you for the feedback!

I think #4207 should get merged as-is, this PR closed, and the few remaining property file changes put into a new commit/branch/PR.

@alopresto If it's either-or I think the most important thing is to validate and throw an error so the behavior doesn't end up being confusing if both are set and the insecure clientPort is ignored. I wouldn't want it to be just a documented behavior.

There is one situation where having both set is useful -- the API for the status commands don't support TLS, but I think this is in the process of being addressed on the ZK side so it should eventually work itself out.

I'll make some notes over in the [NIFI-7203](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NIFI-7203) JIRA.
